## v1.1.2 increment

What v1.1.2 adds, also frozen under the buyer contract:

  - Postgres-first runtime (active when `DATABASE_URL` is set;
    SQLite hot-copy fallback otherwise). Wired through
    `src/lib/pg.ts`. Idempotent migration via
    `scripts/migrate-supabase.mjs`.
  - Block-editor schema layer: `src/components/admin/block-schemas.ts`
    + `src/components/admin/BlockEditor.tsx`. The schema-driven
    forms expand at runtime in `PageBuilder.tsx`. New block-type
    additions go through `cms/blocks/registry.ts` and a matching
    `BlockSchema` case.
  - Per-entity CRUD admin routes that are an addition, not a
    change to existing buyer-visible flow:
      - `src/app/admin/projects/page.tsx` and `[id]/page.tsx`
      - `src/app/admin/journal/page.tsx` and `[id]/page.tsx`
      - `src/app/admin/testimonials/page.tsx` and `[id]/page.tsx`
      - `src/app/admin/team/page.tsx` and `[id]/page.tsx`
  - Media library at `/admin/media` (Phase 3), wired to
    Supabase Storage when configured.
  - Supabase Storage media pipeline under `app/api/media/**`.
  - `scripts/seed-content.mjs` Postgres-or-SQLite seed that
    writes 3 projects / 3 journal / 3 testimonials / 3 team /
    3 media to whichever engine is active.
  - `scripts/smoke-api.mjs` + `smoke-phase{2,5,6,7}.mjs` + the
    pre-existing `smoke.mjs`.

## v1.2.0 increment

What v1.2.0 adds on top of v1.1.2, also frozen:

  - Admin write-path fixes: snake_case row hydration across
    `description_json`, `before_image`, `after_image`,
    `model_3d`, `is_published`, `cover_image`, `content_json`,
    `author_name`. `AdminProjectForm` and `AdminJournalForm`
    read both snake_case and camelCase source keys.
  - Read-side fix: `RichTextRenderer` accepts string OR
    record for `json`. Postgres JSONB path works without
    JSON.parse-throw.
  - Tiered role gate: `requireSuperadmin()` in
    `src/lib/license-gate.ts`. Wired through
    `/api/admin/license` POST and `/api/admin/demo-reset`
    POST. `/api/admin/whoami` exposes role.
  - Cross-coldstart durability: `scripts/smoke-coldstart.mjs`
    proves writes survive a 90-second Vercel Hobby idle
    window when `DATABASE_URL` is set.
  - Spatial walkthrough pin-and-scrub: GSAP ScrollTrigger
    with `pin: true` / `scrub: 1` on the desktop path,
    matchMedia-driven reduced-motion fallback to the
    original horizontal-snap-scroll.
  - Demo seed differentiated before/after photo pairs across
    the three seeded projects.

## Operator carve-out (added to v1.1.0)

The v1.1.0 release introduces operator surfaces that are **not** under the
buyer-visible freeze. These files can be added or edited to support the
superadmin console and Envato onboarding without breaking the buyer promise:

  - `src/app/superadmin/**` (operator console pages)
  - `src/app/api/operator/**` (operator-only routes)
  - `src/app/api/envato/webhook/route.ts` (Envato purchase intake)
  - `src/components/operator/**` (operator-only components)
  - `src/lib/operator-store.ts` (operator data layer)
  - `src/lib/operator-auth.ts` (operator cookie session)
  - `src/lib/tenant-brand.ts` (tenant brand + palette reader)

These surfaces are gated by `SUPERADMIN_EMAIL` + `SUPERADMIN_PASSWORD` env vars.
Buyers do not see them.

