## Why the carve-out exists

v1.0.0 was sold as a buyer-complete artifact. v1.1.2 stacks on top of v1.1.0,
and v1.2.0 layers the production-grade Postgres runtime, the tiered role
gate, and the admin write-path persistence layer:

  - a superadmin console for the studio + Envato onboarding (v1.1.0)
  - a tenant model + theme.distro.json overlay (v1.1.0)
  - white-label-friendly defaults (v1.1.0)
  - Postgres-first runtime with bundled-SQLite fallback (v1.1.2)
  - WordPress-grade admin CRUD per entity (v1.1.2)
  - TipTap rich text + MediaPicker integration (v1.1.2)
  - Production-durable writes + tiered admin/superadmin split (v1.2.0)
  - Admin write-path persistence fix + rich-text reader fix (v1.2.0)

The buyer's rendered site (any GET on `/`, `/projects`, `/journal`, `/install`,
`/admin`) stays in the v1.0.0 contract. The operator surfaces live behind
gated auth and the buyer can never reach them.

